WEBVTT

00:10.311 --> 00:13.112
        [elegant music]

00:20.588 --> 00:24.456
 <i> ¶ The sun may not be shining ¶</i>

00:25.526 --> 00:29.328
  <i> ¶ The moon may not be high ¶</i>

00:30.598 --> 00:35.200
<i>¶ The nighttime sky is cloudy ¶</i>

00:35.202 --> 00:39.538
     <i> ¶ And there's no stars</i>
          <i> In the sky ¶</i>

00:39.540 --> 00:44.576
    <i> ¶ Even though there may</i>
       <i> Be other worlds ¶</i>

00:44.578 --> 00:48.547
    <i> ¶ There's no place that</i>
        <i> I'd rather be ¶</i>

00:48.549 --> 00:55.154
        <i> ¶ C'est la vie,</i>
  <i> C'est la vie, c'est la vie ¶</i>

01:11.205 --> 01:14.606
      [motorcycle revving]

01:15.810 --> 01:19.378
 <i> ¶ So put your arms around me ¶</i>

01:21.082 --> 01:24.383
   <i> ¶ Who knows what will be ¶</i>

01:24.518 --> 01:31.256
        <i> ¶ C'est la vie,</i>
  <i> C'est la vie, c'est la vie ¶</i>

01:46.240 --> 01:49.108
     Harold, I thought that
      you were an autumn,

01:49.110 --> 01:52.144
 and it turns out that you are
    a spring, just like me.

01:55.116 --> 01:58.750
      You look good. See?
 Oh, geez, Mom. You scared me.

01:58.752 --> 02:00.319
    I'm not the one talking
         to a dead guy.

02:00.321 --> 02:01.653
       -What do you want?
           -Upstairs!

02:01.655 --> 02:02.855
       I'm in the middle
    of something right now.

02:02.857 --> 02:04.356
          He can wait!

02:10.631 --> 02:12.531
        Happy birthday!

02:12.533 --> 02:14.266
    No, I'm not celebrating.

02:14.268 --> 02:15.434
          I told you.

02:15.436 --> 02:17.402
       27 hours of labor.

02:17.404 --> 02:19.438
      I think it's more my
        call than yours.

02:19.440 --> 02:21.640
     Your mother preferred
     to stay in even then.

02:22.243 --> 02:23.675
     Okay. Make your wish.

02:24.245 --> 02:25.777
  Wait. Did you even make one?

02:26.180 --> 02:27.513
      I couldn't think of
    anything, you make one.

02:27.515 --> 02:28.680
           Seriously.

02:28.682 --> 02:30.883
             -Mhm.
          -Okay, um...

02:31.318 --> 02:32.251
             Okay.

02:32.253 --> 02:33.852
      -[mom] What was it?
          -Just blow.

02:35.189 --> 02:36.388
           [laughing]

02:36.590 --> 02:37.523
        Nah, ah, ah, ah.

02:37.525 --> 02:38.557
    Other room for presents.

02:39.560 --> 02:40.492
          Frank, now!

02:40.661 --> 02:42.394
Frank that's your cue, come on!

02:45.666 --> 02:47.699
        Oh my God. Mom.

02:47.701 --> 02:49.168
         A blowup doll?

02:49.170 --> 02:50.769
Come on, I'm not that desperate.

02:50.771 --> 02:52.704
       You said that you
       wanted to practice

02:52.706 --> 02:56.508
     some greener embalming
techniques, and maybe teach Sam.

02:56.510 --> 02:58.710
     What do you expect me
    to teach Sam with that?

02:58.712 --> 03:00.746
-He's way better than a banana.
             -Sam.

03:00.748 --> 03:04.750
   Well obviously, I ordered
    the wrong kind of doll.

03:04.752 --> 03:06.218
     But isn't he gorgeous?

03:06.420 --> 03:07.786
    Oh yeah, Gram thinks he
    kind of looks like dad.

03:07.788 --> 03:09.955
             -How?
      -His eyes, no hair.

03:09.957 --> 03:13.192
    Anyway, we kept him, and
     we've named him Pedro.

03:13.194 --> 03:17.896
    Oh, and we have another
        present for you.

03:20.401 --> 03:21.350
     And it's in his pants.

03:21.351 --> 03:22.300
         -And I'm done.
        -Oh Frank, wait.

03:22.303 --> 03:24.303
     Will you to the intake
      for Ann-Marie Toddy?

03:24.305 --> 03:25.437
             Right.

03:26.240 --> 03:27.739
        Okay, his pants?

03:27.741 --> 03:29.241
     [grandma] His pocket.

03:33.914 --> 03:35.881
    -We're going to Moscow!
            -Who is?

03:35.883 --> 03:37.783
        Me and you, Mom!

03:37.785 --> 03:39.251
   Gram booked us on a tour,

03:39.253 --> 03:40.252
 and we're leaving in a month.

03:43.557 --> 03:45.891
     That means "I wish to
       buy some cheese."

03:45.893 --> 03:47.893
      -Or it might mean--
             -Sam--

03:47.895 --> 03:48.827
    That your cheese smells
          like feet--

03:48.829 --> 03:49.795
          Stop please.

03:49.797 --> 03:50.762
    I still don't remember.

03:50.764 --> 03:51.697
     And wait, wait, wait.

03:51.699 --> 03:53.332
    Look, I made a calendar.

03:53.334 --> 03:54.299
          Put it away.

03:54.301 --> 03:57.336
    -Mom, I've been crossing
         off the days--
         -Put it away.

03:57.338 --> 03:58.837
    -So that whenever we get
       close to the day--
       -Put it away now.

04:00.374 --> 04:02.441
             -Mom!
 -Whatever you did, cancel it.

04:03.444 --> 04:05.944
     -How could you get her
      hopes up like this?
      -Don't yell at her.

04:05.946 --> 04:07.746
             -Sam--
   -[Sam] I had as much to do
      with this as she did

04:07.982 --> 04:10.315
      Did you really think
    that this was something
       that was for real?

04:10.384 --> 04:12.484
      You didn't think we
       would actually go?

04:14.288 --> 04:15.520
       No, of course not.

04:16.390 --> 04:17.322
           It's you.

04:17.324 --> 04:20.591
 -[Sam] Just forget about it, I
    don't even care anymore.
       -Oh come on, Sam.

04:24.431 --> 04:25.364
    What were you thinking?

04:25.599 --> 04:27.266
 She has wanted to go to Moscow

04:27.268 --> 04:28.467
 since she learned how to talk.

04:28.469 --> 04:29.635
    Yes, but that's because
           of Peter.

04:29.637 --> 04:31.036
  And Mom, of all the places,

04:31.038 --> 04:32.437
     I mean you know what's
   going on there right now?

04:32.439 --> 04:33.438
    It's kind of a disaster.

04:33.440 --> 04:35.340
 The whole world is a disaster.

04:35.676 --> 04:37.909
      -You have to find a
       way to live in it.
         -Please, Mom,

04:38.979 --> 04:39.695
 I found my way, I like my way,

04:39.696 --> 04:40.412
        -and I'm happy.
         -Good for you.

04:40.414 --> 04:43.048
           -And Sam?
     -Did you have any idea
        that there were

04:43.050 --> 04:45.017
      20,000 homicides in
       Russia last year?

04:45.019 --> 04:46.852
   Do you know that we're in
 the middle of a Cold War 2.0?

04:46.854 --> 04:48.771
You think it's a safe place to--

04:48.772 --> 04:50.689
      It is a plane ticket
       and a plane ride.

04:50.691 --> 04:52.357
 If it was a matter of flipping
   a switch, don't you think

04:52.359 --> 04:53.358
 I would've flipped it by now?

04:53.761 --> 04:54.693
     You have to cancel it.

04:57.431 --> 04:58.430
      Where are you going?

04:58.432 --> 05:00.499
     It is my lottery day.

05:00.501 --> 05:03.902
  Oh, and you have a dead body

05:03.904 --> 05:05.304
  waiting for your downstairs.

05:05.306 --> 05:07.406
     Crap. Ann-Marie Toddy.

05:07.408 --> 05:08.740
       Mom, where are the
        hedge clippers?

05:08.742 --> 05:10.409
          Garden, why?

05:10.411 --> 05:11.910
      'Cause she's too fat
      for the truck cart.

05:12.413 --> 05:13.812
         -[grandma] Oh.
             -What?

05:13.814 --> 05:15.681
      -Everybody does it,
         Dad taught me.
      -[doorbell ringing]

05:15.683 --> 05:17.549
    Well, it's going to take
        about a thousand

05:17.551 --> 05:20.485
cute little kitten videos to get
   that image out of my head.

05:23.324 --> 05:25.023
           -Hey guys!
          -[woman] Hi!

05:25.025 --> 05:27.059
           Hi, Molly!

05:27.061 --> 05:28.760
     Hi, Suz, looking good!

05:28.762 --> 05:31.663
  Don't I know it! [laughing]

05:31.665 --> 05:34.566
 Mom, will you grab those hedge
 clippers for me before you go?

05:34.568 --> 05:36.635
      They're right there,
     next to the geraniums.

05:36.637 --> 05:37.769
        Are you serious?

05:37.771 --> 05:39.871
 [speaking in foreign language]

05:39.873 --> 05:42.841
      -The lottery calls.
     -You know you're 9,000
       times more likely

05:42.843 --> 05:44.910
    to get hit by lightning
than you are to win the lottery.

05:44.912 --> 05:48.380
   It's just for fun, Molly.
         Remember fun?

05:48.549 --> 05:51.116
           -Woo hoo!
    -[Susan] We're gonna do
         it this time!

06:02.062 --> 06:04.863
         [catchy music]

06:07.568 --> 06:08.500
       Don't stare at me.

06:12.706 --> 06:14.740
        [doorbell rings]

06:18.979 --> 06:19.911
              Sam?

06:23.117 --> 06:24.049
              Sam!

06:25.619 --> 06:26.551
              Sam?

06:27.888 --> 06:28.987
             Mama!

06:29.690 --> 06:30.622
          Knock much?

06:30.624 --> 06:31.957
 There's somebody at the door.

06:31.959 --> 06:32.924
              So?

06:34.528 --> 06:36.928
       So, Frank is out,
         and Grandma's
    getting a lotto ticket.

06:36.930 --> 06:38.597
       Why don't you get
       him to answer it?

06:38.599 --> 06:39.931
     Answer the door, Sam.

06:39.933 --> 06:41.166
      Come to Moscow, Mom.

06:41.668 --> 06:42.601
            Come on!

06:43.637 --> 06:44.386
              No.

06:44.387 --> 06:45.136
[scoffs] Not anymore, I'm done.

06:46.073 --> 06:47.005
              Ugh.

06:47.574 --> 06:48.740
          [Sam sighs]

06:57.651 --> 06:58.583
        [doorbell rings]

07:06.827 --> 07:07.759
             Okay.

07:08.929 --> 07:10.095
            -Sorry.
              -Hi.

07:11.598 --> 07:14.199
  Hi, I'm Joe... Frederickson.

07:14.201 --> 07:19.104
   My father's... visitation
       is this afternoon,

07:19.106 --> 07:20.572
      Harold Frederickson.

07:20.574 --> 07:23.508
   Well, the parlor entrance
    is just around the side.

07:23.510 --> 07:25.010
  Tried that, no one answered.

07:25.212 --> 07:27.646
  Well that's because I think
     you're a little early.

07:28.849 --> 07:31.817
      -Is that a problem?
      -You know, my mother
  usually handles this stuff,

07:31.819 --> 07:33.485
      and she's not here.

07:33.487 --> 07:34.619
   I'm sorry, you know what?

07:34.621 --> 07:35.821
    No, it's not a problem.

07:36.924 --> 07:38.824
Just, if you go around the side,

07:38.826 --> 07:39.758
   I'll make sure it's open.

07:42.863 --> 07:45.163
    Oh, wait, before you go,

07:45.165 --> 07:47.999
      could you grab those
     hedge clippers for me?

07:50.504 --> 07:51.236
             Sure.

08:02.916 --> 08:03.849
           Thank you.

08:03.850 --> 08:04.783
           -That way.
       -Oh, yeah, got it.

08:10.224 --> 08:11.823
      [lighthearted music]

08:22.035 --> 08:22.968
          Don't start.

08:22.970 --> 08:25.237
 -Why is the door still locked?
          -He's early.

08:25.772 --> 08:27.639
          -Unlock it.
        -I already did.

08:27.975 --> 08:29.641
     -Okay, go get dressed.
             -What?

08:29.643 --> 08:31.076
        Here, take this.

08:41.755 --> 08:44.756
      That was Frank, and
       he'll be handling
     your father's service.

08:45.225 --> 08:47.592
   I really wanted to see him

08:47.594 --> 08:48.827
    before you did all that.

08:50.163 --> 08:51.096
              Oh.

08:51.098 --> 08:55.800
 You know, you think you would,
         but trust me,
     it is better this way.

08:57.871 --> 08:59.137
    What color is his face?

09:00.140 --> 09:01.306
    Beige bisque number 40.

09:01.308 --> 09:06.211
      I wanted to see him,
not some made up version of him.

09:06.213 --> 09:08.246
       I can change it if
       you'd like me to.

09:08.782 --> 09:10.916
            No, no.

09:13.854 --> 09:15.921
     I'm sorry, it's fine.

09:18.025 --> 09:18.957
             Fine.

09:19.026 --> 09:20.292
   Well, you'd be the first.

09:21.295 --> 09:23.628
       We aren't built to
       be fine with this.

09:24.264 --> 09:26.731
           [mumbles]

09:27.634 --> 09:30.135
I'd also like to read a passage.

09:31.738 --> 09:34.739
   When everybody gets here,
  from "A Calendar of Wisdom".

09:34.741 --> 09:35.674
            Tolstoy.

09:37.744 --> 09:38.677
             Yeah.

09:39.746 --> 09:40.679
             Yeah.

09:42.249 --> 09:44.616
   -Is that going to be here?
              -No.

09:44.818 --> 09:46.685
         -What is that?
        -A training aid.

09:49.222 --> 09:50.155
            [gasps]

09:52.826 --> 09:53.758
             What?

09:54.828 --> 09:55.760
             Um...

09:59.232 --> 10:01.132
  I just had too much coffee.

10:07.808 --> 10:08.740
         What's wrong?

10:14.247 --> 10:15.180
         Are you okay?

10:16.316 --> 10:17.282
          No, I'm not.

10:30.631 --> 10:31.363
       Oh, I'm so sorry.

10:34.368 --> 10:36.935
      I'm going to let you
    have some time with him.

10:37.804 --> 10:40.672
      Your father, not the
        doll, obviously.

10:40.674 --> 10:42.040
  That would be really weird.

10:42.876 --> 10:44.909
    I will be down the hall,

10:45.012 --> 10:47.212
  and Frank should be in soon.

10:47.214 --> 10:49.347
 -Wait, wait. What's your name?
            -Molly.

10:50.384 --> 10:51.316
             Molly.

10:56.723 --> 10:57.989
            [sighs]

11:05.699 --> 11:07.932
   Wow. Way too much coffee.

11:11.304 --> 11:12.237
           Aw, shit.

11:13.206 --> 11:15.874
     Oh, shit, shit, shit.

11:18.278 --> 11:19.811
What are you doing to his face?

11:19.813 --> 11:20.912
        It's all wrong!

11:20.914 --> 11:22.147
         It's not him.

11:23.884 --> 11:25.350
 Of course it's not him, right?

11:26.319 --> 11:29.354
       It's some place he
       used to hang out.

11:29.356 --> 11:30.689
     An abandoned building.

11:32.092 --> 11:33.024
     How did you know him?

11:33.160 --> 11:35.994
    Oh, um, I don't, didn't.

11:35.996 --> 11:38.830
       I just live here,

11:38.832 --> 11:40.699
      and I'm not supposed
        to be down here

11:40.701 --> 11:42.167
   when there are people, so.

11:42.369 --> 11:43.768
Could I have his tie clip back?

11:46.139 --> 11:47.072
             What?

11:47.908 --> 11:48.840
     The one on your head.

11:50.143 --> 11:54.112
Oh, it's a barrette, it's mine.

11:54.114 --> 11:57.115
       I made it for him,
        in Eagle Scouts.

11:57.250 --> 11:58.383
  It's got my initials on it.

12:04.224 --> 12:05.890
     J.F. Joe Frederickson.

12:06.326 --> 12:08.193
         I must, um...

12:08.929 --> 12:10.795
[nervous laugh] I don't know how
    that got here, it just--

12:10.864 --> 12:13.465
       Probably happened
       when you took it.

12:17.370 --> 12:18.303
     Are you going to tell?

12:19.339 --> 12:21.206
        -I wasn't there.
            -Where?

12:21.408 --> 12:22.340
           When he...

12:25.879 --> 12:28.012
      Working. Working...

12:29.149 --> 12:30.181
      Out of the country.

12:32.085 --> 12:33.017
             Whoa!

12:33.787 --> 12:36.154
 Did he... Did he just breathe?

12:37.491 --> 12:41.226
            Oh, no.
       It just looks like
        that sometimes.

12:41.762 --> 12:42.494
    He didn't, don't worry.

12:45.365 --> 12:46.397
             So...

12:48.869 --> 12:49.868
Why were you out of the country?

12:52.839 --> 12:53.805
     I make documentaries.

12:55.942 --> 12:59.544
Oh my God, I'm like so addicted
   to the Discovery Channel.

12:59.546 --> 13:01.346
       -Would I have seen
       anything of yours?
           -Possibly.

13:06.253 --> 13:08.019
     You know, it's so cool
    that you get to travel.

13:08.822 --> 13:10.555
    I was supposed to go to
     Moscow in a few weeks

13:10.557 --> 13:12.223
     and I got a passport,

13:12.225 --> 13:14.459
  and I was learning Russian,
          and then...

13:17.197 --> 13:18.997
   You know what, I'm sorry.

13:18.999 --> 13:21.199
 I should just leave you alone.

13:24.871 --> 13:26.971
      It was nice to meet
        you, by the way.

13:27.974 --> 13:29.407
 And I'm sorry about your dad.

13:30.310 --> 13:33.244
       Um, is this weird?

13:34.447 --> 13:35.380
          Not really.

13:36.550 --> 13:37.482
            Thanks.

13:37.984 --> 13:38.917
            About...

13:40.120 --> 13:41.085
      About what I did...

13:41.087 --> 13:43.021
    I don't know what you're
         talking about.

13:55.869 --> 13:56.601
     [Joe] Good to see you.

13:56.870 --> 13:58.336
   Thank you, appreciate it.

13:58.338 --> 13:59.270
           Thank you.

14:00.574 --> 14:02.540
      Thank you, thank you
        for being here,

14:02.542 --> 14:03.575
    I really appreciate it.

14:03.577 --> 14:05.076
 Thanks for coming all the way.

14:12.052 --> 14:12.984
       [Joe] Hey, Buddy.

14:13.320 --> 14:14.519
  Yeah, yeah, good to see you.

14:14.521 --> 14:15.520
          Be careful.

14:21.461 --> 14:23.361
   What a beautiful necklace,
           Ann-Marie.

14:24.030 --> 14:24.963
            Gorgeous

14:24.965 --> 14:28.099
   All right, I wanted a good
  picture to work from but...

14:30.036 --> 14:31.069
       And it's expired.

14:31.538 --> 14:33.171
     Still talking to them?

14:34.975 --> 14:36.441
 You know that's creepy, right?

14:39.145 --> 14:40.411
        Molly, it's me!

14:41.114 --> 14:42.046
             Molly!

14:47.954 --> 14:50.955
      [suspenseful music]

14:57.564 --> 14:58.963
        It's okay, Mom.

15:02.602 --> 15:04.602
           One, two,

15:07.274 --> 15:08.206
             three.

15:13.546 --> 15:14.479
           It's okay.

15:15.682 --> 15:17.548
     It's okay, it's okay.

15:20.553 --> 15:21.486
            Oh, God.

15:25.392 --> 15:26.624
        I'm sorry, Sam.

15:28.461 --> 15:29.394
            I know.

15:40.273 --> 15:42.473
 I'm sorry I was gone so long.
     Come here, let's eat.

15:44.044 --> 15:44.976
           Come here.

15:46.513 --> 15:49.547
         [dog panting]

15:49.549 --> 15:50.682
           Atta boy.

15:51.952 --> 15:53.117
       That's a good boy.

15:54.587 --> 15:56.054
            Not yet.

15:56.056 --> 15:59.257
     [calming jazzy music]

16:13.306 --> 16:14.706
       Hey, here you go.

16:18.345 --> 16:21.045
         [somber music]

16:25.752 --> 16:27.085
 Do you know what the movie is?

16:27.087 --> 16:30.221
  You have to go on this trip,
     Molly. Do you hear me?

16:30.223 --> 16:31.723
  You have to take this trip.

16:33.093 --> 16:35.493
     [Sam] Mom, Gram, hurry
     up, it's movie night.

16:35.495 --> 16:37.228
    You hear that? Let's go.

16:37.664 --> 16:39.697
     [grandma] So what are
      we watching tonight?

16:41.301 --> 16:42.567
     You know that guy that
        was here today?

16:42.769 --> 16:45.236
   The kind of hot one, Joe.

16:45.238 --> 16:47.372
        -What about him?
    -He makes documentaries,

16:47.374 --> 16:48.773
   and I found one on demand.

16:48.775 --> 16:50.541
     It's about cruelty to
      animals in circuses

16:50.543 --> 16:52.377
      and animal shows all
        over the world.

16:52.746 --> 16:55.213
      One of them is about
    the Moscow Cat Theater.

16:56.149 --> 17:00.018
   -So, he's been to Russia,
       which is so cool.
   -When did you talk to him?

17:00.020 --> 17:01.652
           -Earlier.
  -And you thought he was hot?

17:01.721 --> 17:03.721
     I don't know, kind of
    like someone's dad hot.

17:03.723 --> 17:06.023
           Oh, and...

17:06.760 --> 17:08.291
         I got us hats.

17:08.294 --> 17:09.227
         [grandma] Aw.

17:09.561 --> 17:11.695
       One for you, Mama.

17:11.698 --> 17:13.131
   And one for you,<i> Babushka.</i>

17:13.133 --> 17:14.464
      Thank you, darling.

17:14.467 --> 17:15.400
              Mhm.

17:16.336 --> 17:19.470
      [lighthearted music]

17:22.142 --> 17:25.042
     I ordered them when I
    thought we would still--

17:25.310 --> 17:27.178
          -Sam, I'm--
        -No, it's okay.

17:27.513 --> 17:28.445
        One more thing.

17:34.554 --> 17:36.821
           [laughing]

17:38.324 --> 17:39.424
       Here's your date.

17:39.426 --> 17:41.092
           [laughing]

17:43.463 --> 17:45.063
   [woman] <i> Every kid's dream</i>
         <i> is to run away</i>

17:45.065 --> 17:46.330
  <i> and join the circus, right?</i>

17:46.332 --> 17:49.233
    <i> Well, I actually did it,</i>
   <i> as a grown up, but still.</i>

17:49.235 --> 17:52.804
     <i> I left my whole life.</i>
    <i> Then a dream just turned</i>
       <i> into a nightmare.</i>

17:57.610 --> 17:59.610
  [interviewer] <i> And what made</i>
  <i> you decide to come forward?</i>

18:00.346 --> 18:01.579
      <i> The circus is a lie.</i>

18:02.315 --> 18:03.247
             Molls.

18:05.385 --> 18:09.220
      [lighthearted music]

18:09.489 --> 18:11.155
    Are you really thinking
          about going?

18:12.158 --> 18:13.825
      You don't even go to
       the grocery store.

18:15.161 --> 18:17.628
  You couldn't even take a few
 steps outside this afternoon.

18:26.106 --> 18:27.105
        You're not real.

18:31.478 --> 18:32.410
         This is real.

18:53.166 --> 18:55.766
        [siren blaring]

19:13.520 --> 19:14.452
              Sam.

19:18.424 --> 19:19.357
            Wake up.

19:19.826 --> 19:20.758
              Sam.

19:21.327 --> 19:22.260
             What?

19:22.328 --> 19:23.261
          We're going.

19:24.597 --> 19:25.530
          Going where?

19:25.765 --> 19:26.731
           To Moscow.

19:28.668 --> 19:30.601
         -We're going.
            -Really?

19:33.239 --> 19:34.672
    Really, really, really?

19:35.542 --> 19:36.874
      Just the two of us.

19:36.876 --> 19:37.808
            But how?

19:37.810 --> 19:40.912
       I don't know yet,
        but we're going.

19:43.883 --> 19:44.882
             Okay.

19:45.885 --> 19:46.918
        I love you, Mom.

19:46.920 --> 19:48.219
        I love you too.

19:48.721 --> 19:49.787
          Go to sleep.

20:11.744 --> 20:16.347
       <i> ¶ If I can't have</i>
   <i> Everything I wished for ¶</i>

20:21.621 --> 20:26.857
    <i> ¶ At least there's more</i>
     <i> Left for me to dream ¶</i>

20:29.696 --> 20:31.662
        <i> ¶ C'est la vie ¶</i>

20:35.268 --> 20:37.268
        <i> ¶ C'est la vie ¶</i>

20:38.338 --> 20:39.737
   Is something burning, Mom?

20:39.839 --> 20:41.572
           No... Yes.

20:45.011 --> 20:46.844
       [Molly] Oh my God.

20:46.846 --> 20:48.613
     -Oh my, get me the...
            -Got it.

20:48.615 --> 20:49.714
             -Yeah.
             -Here.

20:51.384 --> 20:52.683
              Ugh.

20:52.685 --> 20:54.919
           [coughing]

20:54.921 --> 20:57.555
           [beeping]

20:57.724 --> 21:00.691
 [Sam] Take the batteries out.
         -[Molly] What?
 -[grandma] What is happening?

21:00.693 --> 21:02.293
          On the side,
         give it to me.

21:02.295 --> 21:04.495
           [beeping]

21:05.431 --> 21:08.032
        [intense music]

21:17.810 --> 21:20.711
    -What were you cooking?
       -I wasn't cooking.

21:20.813 --> 21:22.713
         What? Then how
     did that get in there?

21:22.715 --> 21:23.714
  Were you cooking something?

21:23.950 --> 21:25.650
     An oven mitt, I guess.

21:25.652 --> 21:27.351
     Hey, grab your shoes,
          we're late!

21:27.353 --> 21:28.486
         I'll get Oleg.

21:29.489 --> 21:31.389
 Oleg? I thought it was Pedro.

21:32.292 --> 21:34.058
     I rechristened him in
      honor of your trip.

21:34.794 --> 21:36.761
  Someone was careless enough

21:36.763 --> 21:39.363
    to throw their birthday
       gift in the trash,

21:39.365 --> 21:40.898
      so I liberated him.

21:40.900 --> 21:42.533
        In a new outfit?

21:42.535 --> 21:44.335
       -He needed a bath.
              -Hm.

21:44.570 --> 21:46.304
    He's not coming with us.

21:46.306 --> 21:47.838
  Oleg loves riding in a car.

21:47.840 --> 21:49.774
      I'm just going to go
        open the windows

21:49.776 --> 21:50.741
 so he can stick his head out.

21:51.577 --> 21:52.810
       That's dogs, Mom.

21:55.448 --> 21:56.380
      I'll go to my room.

21:56.983 --> 21:57.915
           Your room?

21:57.917 --> 22:01.452
   -But Gram, we have to go.
           -Go where?

22:01.921 --> 22:02.853
        Dress rehearsal.

22:02.855 --> 22:05.089
           Oh my God.
    Get her, Sam, grab her.

22:05.591 --> 22:06.991
      Mama, Mom, you okay?

22:06.993 --> 22:07.992
              Oh.

22:07.994 --> 22:09.660
         Oh, I'm fine.

22:09.662 --> 22:11.462
        [doorbell rings]

22:11.464 --> 22:12.396
    Sam, will you get that?

22:15.401 --> 22:17.802
       Mom, I'm going to
        call Dr. Barlow.

22:17.804 --> 22:18.969
            Oh, no.

22:18.971 --> 22:20.838
 I just forgot to eat breakfast

22:20.840 --> 22:22.840
       so I took my blood
         pressure pills

22:22.842 --> 22:23.874
      on an empty stomach.

22:24.010 --> 22:25.543
           I'm fine.

22:29.716 --> 22:31.082
   I'm sorry, this is crazy.

22:31.084 --> 22:33.417
  So crazy to bring him here.

22:33.419 --> 22:34.552
              Mom?

22:35.588 --> 22:37.021
      Joe. What happened?

22:37.023 --> 22:38.122
           It's Tuck.

22:38.124 --> 22:40.124
 He was just lying there cold.

22:40.126 --> 22:42.026
    And I was going to bury
      him in the backyard,

22:42.028 --> 22:44.462
        but I thought my
       condo association
      would frown on that.

22:45.064 --> 22:48.399
      Oh, I don't do pets.
       I don't even know
       if that's allowed.

22:48.401 --> 22:50.134
      Honey, you just cut
    open a plus-sized woman

22:50.136 --> 22:52.002
 with a pair of garden shears.

22:52.004 --> 22:53.938
    You're not going to help
  this poor man with his dog?

22:53.940 --> 22:54.939
      And I couldn't just
       dump him somewhere

22:54.941 --> 22:56.006
    because he was a rescue,

22:56.008 --> 22:57.475
 and he has abandonment issues.

22:57.477 --> 22:58.509
  Honey, we have to get going,

22:58.511 --> 22:59.443
  you're going to be so late!

22:59.579 --> 23:01.445
        Joe can take me.

23:01.447 --> 23:02.780
          -Right, Joe?
              -No.

23:04.417 --> 23:05.383
  Well, why don't you take me?

23:06.652 --> 23:08.452
 -How many points do you have?
            -Points?

23:08.454 --> 23:10.454
   -[Molly] On your license.
             -None.

23:10.456 --> 23:11.589
      How do you do that?

23:11.591 --> 23:12.723
          -I've got--
       -You have so many.

23:12.725 --> 23:14.759
    -I'm a very good driver.
 -I'm going to be so, so late.

23:16.162 --> 23:17.495
      Okay, I'll take him.

23:18.865 --> 23:21.065
    And I'll do what I can,
    but I can't embalm him.

23:21.134 --> 23:23.401
   No, no, that's not what I,
        I didn't mean...

23:27.840 --> 23:29.840
     I didn't have anywhere
          else to go.

23:33.079 --> 23:34.011
        He's my family.

23:36.082 --> 23:37.014
             Okay.

23:38.184 --> 23:39.884
     It's okay. I got him.

23:40.686 --> 23:41.619
           Thank you.

23:41.888 --> 23:43.020
           -Bye, Sam.
             -Bye.

23:44.891 --> 23:47.057
   -[grandma] Honey, I'll see
   you later at the recital.
             -Okay.

23:55.501 --> 23:56.434
          [door shuts]

23:57.136 --> 23:58.602
  I brought you some company.

23:59.005 --> 23:59.937
           Oh, great.

24:03.709 --> 24:05.843
     What do you think he's
     going to do with him?
You think he's going to keep him

24:05.845 --> 24:07.478
      like Roy Rogers did
         with Trigger?

24:07.480 --> 24:08.512
       I don't know, Mom,

24:08.514 --> 24:09.780
     I'm not a taxidermist.

24:10.716 --> 24:13.517
Your mother must think I'm nuts.

24:15.688 --> 24:18.055
      Well, glass houses.

24:19.492 --> 24:20.524
       What do you mean?

24:20.993 --> 24:21.926
          [chuckling]

24:23.196 --> 24:24.128
            Nothing.

24:26.933 --> 24:27.865
            Do you?

24:29.602 --> 24:31.035
        Think I'm nuts?

24:34.240 --> 24:35.239
        I've seen worse.

24:36.175 --> 24:37.575
   I don't want you driving.

24:37.743 --> 24:39.577
 I am not missing that recital.

24:39.946 --> 24:43.214
             Okay.
     Doctor first, and then
     Frank will drive you,

24:43.216 --> 24:44.882
        -you promise me?
              -No.

24:45.051 --> 24:47.518
     Stop treating me like
         an old person.

24:47.520 --> 24:49.153
     I've got at least ten
      good years before...

24:49.822 --> 24:51.922
       -70 is the new 60.
            -Mom...

24:52.892 --> 24:53.824
         Come with me.

24:54.060 --> 24:55.593
       You know I can't!

24:55.595 --> 24:56.927
     You don't have to come
         to the office,

24:56.996 --> 24:59.063
   -you can stay in the car.
     -Frank will drive you.

24:59.065 --> 25:01.999
     You told Sam that you
     would go on this trip.

25:02.001 --> 25:03.634
    How do you think you're
        going to make it

25:03.636 --> 25:06.070
if you can't even go four miles
    to the doctor's office.

25:07.573 --> 25:08.572
          Molly, I...

25:12.044 --> 25:12.977
          I need you.

25:14.547 --> 25:15.546
      Not Frank this time.

25:17.884 --> 25:18.816
              You.

25:19.719 --> 25:20.651
             Okay.

25:21.521 --> 25:24.655
      [lighthearted music]

25:26.659 --> 25:28.692
      What's the strangest
    thing you've ever seen?

25:32.064 --> 25:33.831
 Why do you make documentaries?

25:35.568 --> 25:36.300
            I, um...

25:38.804 --> 25:41.639
          I think I'm
     a pretty good witness
    of other people's lives,

25:41.641 --> 25:43.040
    other people's moments.

25:46.579 --> 25:48.112
 That's the pretentious answer.

25:50.216 --> 25:53.183
     The real answer is I'm
        more comfortable

25:53.185 --> 25:56.086
   with a camera in front of
   my face than without one.

26:01.827 --> 26:02.927
 Are you sure you want to hear?

26:02.929 --> 26:07.965
   'Cause it's about a ten on
  the crazy ways to die scale.

26:09.902 --> 26:10.834
         Then I'm sure.

26:10.836 --> 26:13.070
[Sam] <i> So there was this pigeon.</i>

26:13.072 --> 26:14.838
    <i> This pigeon who clearly</i>

26:14.840 --> 26:17.808
    <i> did not do his homework</i>
<i>in regards to peanut allergies,</i>

26:18.010 --> 26:21.145
 <i> and who obviously did not know</i>

26:21.147 --> 26:23.647
       that even a whiff
       of the tiny legume

26:23.649 --> 26:26.317
      can send some people
    into anaphylactic shock.

26:27.019 --> 26:29.587
    That dumb bird could've
  had no way of knowing that.

26:30.056 --> 26:32.723
   When he ate those peanuts
         in that park,

26:33.059 --> 26:37.127
he was however unintentionally,
    committing manslaughter.

26:37.697 --> 26:40.598
     47 people were killed
    by lightning that year.

26:41.200 --> 26:43.200
   75 by cataclysmic storms,

26:45.171 --> 26:47.771
 <i> and as far as I know, only one</i>

26:47.773 --> 26:51.175
    <i> has ever been killed by</i>
  <i> peanut infested pigeon poop.</i>

26:51.177 --> 26:54.078
           [laughing]

26:54.280 --> 26:57.781
  <i> Would've been a lot funnier</i>
      <i> if it wasn't my dad.</i>

26:59.752 --> 27:00.684
              Sam.

27:02.088 --> 27:03.020
             Yeah?

27:03.823 --> 27:05.322
 I'm pretty sure that's an 11.

27:08.728 --> 27:09.660
           At least.

27:16.969 --> 27:18.002
       I'm really sorry.

27:29.315 --> 27:31.148
     I can't believe you're
     doing this guy's dog,

27:31.150 --> 27:32.116
     you didn't even do me.

27:32.118 --> 27:33.417
    You just farmed me out.

27:33.419 --> 27:35.953
 You're spending all this time
   brushing this dog's hair,

27:35.955 --> 27:38.322
      and you didn't even
    spend a second with me.

27:38.324 --> 27:39.890
      Just threw me in the
       trash last night.

27:39.892 --> 27:41.759
   -I am not talking to you.
           -Why not?

27:41.761 --> 27:43.927
-Because I refuse to be insane.
      -Well, I don't think

27:43.929 --> 27:45.295
    you really have a choice
    on that matter, do you?

27:45.297 --> 27:46.664
        [grandma] <i> Molly!</i>

27:46.666 --> 27:48.032
           -Oh, shit.
             -What?

27:48.334 --> 27:49.266
  Where are you going, Molly?

27:52.805 --> 27:53.737
         I want to go.

27:53.739 --> 27:55.072
           [grandma]
    You can do this, Molly.

27:55.074 --> 27:57.074
 I have faith in you, come on.

27:57.343 --> 27:58.976
    Just one step at a time.

28:02.248 --> 28:04.081
   That's it, yes. That's it!

28:04.083 --> 28:05.916
       -No, I can't, Mom.
     -But if you just do--

28:05.918 --> 28:07.918
           -I can't!
         -Yes, you can!

28:07.920 --> 28:10.054
       -Get off my back!
    -I can't do it, I can't!

28:15.995 --> 28:17.061
      Where are you going?

28:21.133 --> 28:23.801
      What are you doing?
 What are you doing with that?

28:23.969 --> 28:25.102
         Carpool lane.

28:30.009 --> 28:32.743
         [catchy music]

28:36.449 --> 28:37.881
       You almost hit me!

28:37.883 --> 28:39.383
What are you doing, you lunatic?

28:40.019 --> 28:41.285
        I'm driving you.

28:41.287 --> 28:43.020
          -What the--
         -Molly called.

28:43.022 --> 28:45.422
     Guess she wanted me on
     standby, just in case.

28:45.491 --> 28:47.257
         Just in case.
    Oh hey, can I have that?

28:47.993 --> 28:50.160
 You quit 20 years ago, you're
 supposed to be my inspiration.

28:50.162 --> 28:51.795
Yeah, some inspiration, come on.

28:51.797 --> 28:53.030
 It's not like I ever light it.

28:53.132 --> 28:54.364
      Then give it to me.

28:55.267 --> 28:56.366
      I only have the one.

28:58.437 --> 29:01.171
         [catchy music]

29:03.042 --> 29:05.309
      <i> ¶ Hey little girl is</i>
      <i> Your daddy's home ¶</i>

29:05.311 --> 29:07.511
<i>¶ Going to leave me all alone ¶</i>

29:07.513 --> 29:10.247
    <i> ¶ Step outside, let the</i>
       <i> Going wind blow ¶</i>

29:10.349 --> 29:13.117
        [engine starts]

29:14.353 --> 29:17.154
      <i> ¶ Gotta go live like</i>
   <i> We're never going to die ¶</i>

29:18.457 --> 29:21.425
       <i> ¶ Gotta go live ¶</i>

29:23.095 --> 29:26.196
You know how some dogs will run

29:26.198 --> 29:27.998
    or bark in their sleep?

29:30.436 --> 29:31.368
           Not Tuck.

29:31.370 --> 29:35.139
      Tuck, when he slept,
         he would sing.

29:36.809 --> 29:43.080
          -Sing what?
  -I'm tone deaf, but I swear
    it was a howling version

29:43.082 --> 29:44.014
    of "Stairway to Heaven".

29:50.556 --> 29:51.488
              Wow.

29:52.224 --> 29:53.423
  Why does this hurt so much?

29:56.028 --> 29:58.362
     With my dad I was just
       numb, but this...

30:01.967 --> 30:02.966
           Pure pain.

30:05.404 --> 30:07.571
I think pets give us permission.

30:11.110 --> 30:13.977
   What you did for me today,

30:16.215 --> 30:17.915
    not many people would've
           done that.

30:17.917 --> 30:19.883
   Oh, it was nothing really.

30:20.853 --> 30:23.587
      I cleaned him up and
        brushed his fur.

30:24.557 --> 30:27.891
      [lighthearted music]

30:30.095 --> 30:32.329
      How do you know that
          this is what

30:32.331 --> 30:33.497
you wanted to do with your life?

30:35.367 --> 30:37.100
    Not every little girl's
        dream, you mean?

30:38.304 --> 30:40.437
     Well, for me, it was.

30:40.973 --> 30:43.574
  And this is my dad's place,

30:44.043 --> 30:46.043
and he wanted a son, he had me,

30:46.045 --> 30:48.178
    so he taught me instead.

30:49.148 --> 30:52.583
     And I would run around
     embalming my Barbies.

30:56.155 --> 30:57.487
           [laughing]

30:59.558 --> 31:00.490
             You...

31:02.194 --> 31:04.528
         -You're so...
             -What?

31:04.530 --> 31:05.863
            Nothing.

31:08.234 --> 31:09.166
              Oh.

31:10.035 --> 31:11.501
       No, no, I don't...

31:12.504 --> 31:16.573
      I didn't mean you're
       nothing, you're...

31:19.178 --> 31:20.110
           You're...

31:21.280 --> 31:24.047
      [lighthearted music]

31:28.020 --> 31:29.286
 The strangest girl I ever met.

31:30.122 --> 31:32.256
     There's a pet cemetery
         over on Grove.

31:32.258 --> 31:34.491
 It's pretty, it's like a park.
   I could give them a call.

31:35.027 --> 31:36.159
        No, no, no, no.

31:37.296 --> 31:38.228
      I got it from here.

31:38.397 --> 31:39.329
             Okay.

31:43.669 --> 31:45.135
         Come on, boy.

31:48.240 --> 31:49.172
              Joe?

31:50.376 --> 31:51.975
 I'm sorry I keep kissing you.

31:53.412 --> 31:54.344
            I'm not.

31:55.381 --> 31:58.448
      [lighthearted music]

32:13.265 --> 32:14.665
     Where's your necklace?

32:28.514 --> 32:30.147
              -So?
             -What?

32:31.216 --> 32:33.016
  So, what did the doctor say?

32:33.619 --> 32:36.053
   If you were so interested,
   you could've come with me.

32:36.055 --> 32:37.287
     Mom, what did she say?

32:38.524 --> 32:40.657
     What they always say,
       I need more tests.

32:41.493 --> 32:44.695
        You were gone an
       awfully long time
   to just hear "More tests".

32:44.697 --> 32:47.464
Yeah, well, Frank and I stopped
    at Loomer's for a drink.

32:47.733 --> 32:51.201
     Oh, and Pedro here was
 very popular with the bikers.

32:51.203 --> 32:53.503
    Don't make me ask Frank
     what the doctor said,
        because I will.

32:55.607 --> 32:57.274
They think it was a mini stroke,

32:57.743 --> 33:00.143
and that can affect your balance
        and your memory.

33:01.013 --> 33:02.145
            Stroke?

33:05.117 --> 33:08.018
  -I have to cancel the trip.
     -Don't you dare use me

33:08.020 --> 33:09.720
      to get out of this.
        Don't you dare.

33:09.722 --> 33:11.655
 You need to sort yourself out.

33:11.657 --> 33:13.390
     You had a stroke, Mom.

33:13.392 --> 33:15.359
        That's serious!
           A stroke!

33:15.361 --> 33:16.360
    I did not have a stroke.

33:16.362 --> 33:17.694
           -You did!
              -No!

33:18.263 --> 33:19.196
              Sam.

33:21.166 --> 33:23.100
       I called you about
        a hundred times.

33:24.069 --> 33:25.235
          The recital.

33:27.039 --> 33:28.105
           I forgot.

33:29.274 --> 33:32.376
   I'm so sorry, sweetheart,
         I just forgot.

33:33.178 --> 33:34.111
         Are you dying?

33:34.580 --> 33:35.612
              No!

33:35.614 --> 33:36.580
              No.

33:36.582 --> 33:39.182
        Oh no, it sounds
       worse than it is,

33:39.184 --> 33:42.619
they just have to run some tests
      to see what's going
        on in my noggin.

33:43.288 --> 33:44.621
  Oh, that's all it is, honey.

33:47.559 --> 33:48.492
              Sam!

33:49.495 --> 33:52.229
         [somber music]

33:56.568 --> 33:57.501
             Peter.

33:58.370 --> 34:00.303
   Are you there? I need you!

34:02.074 --> 34:03.507
          -[knocking]
             -Sam.

34:05.110 --> 34:06.176
           [knocking]

34:06.345 --> 34:07.711
       Sam, can we talk?

34:09.081 --> 34:10.380
    [Sam] <i> Can we talk later?</i>

34:11.683 --> 34:12.681
          Sure, honey.

34:14.485 --> 34:15.418
          I love you.

34:15.554 --> 34:17.054
     I love you too, Gram.

34:27.800 --> 34:29.065
        You okay, Molls?

34:34.206 --> 34:35.472
          You're here.

34:35.774 --> 34:37.340
   All you had to do was ask.

34:39.844 --> 34:41.511
   But I did it, not before.

34:41.513 --> 34:43.112
   Yeah, maybe not out loud.

34:47.119 --> 34:48.552
If anything happens to my mom--

34:48.754 --> 34:51.521
            I know.
I know, I know, I know, I know.

34:58.564 --> 34:59.830
       Is it really you?

35:03.368 --> 35:05.469
  I want it so much to be you.

35:07.506 --> 35:10.240
Even if it means taking a little
 flight over the cuckoo's nest?

35:10.576 --> 35:13.643
     It doesn't feel crazy,
         it feels real.

35:13.712 --> 35:14.744
        Then I'll stay.

35:15.581 --> 35:16.713
     Then I'll stay, Molls.

35:26.325 --> 35:27.491
         I missed you.

35:30.195 --> 35:33.897
      Did you really think
 something as trivial as dying

35:33.899 --> 35:35.265
      would keep us apart?

35:36.835 --> 35:37.767
              Hm?

35:38.804 --> 35:40.403
           -Did you?
              -No.

35:40.706 --> 35:42.539
          [chuckling]

35:43.342 --> 35:44.474
      I love you so much.

35:46.311 --> 35:47.310
          I love you.

35:49.148 --> 35:51.681
         [catchy music]

36:08.200 --> 36:10.901
  Hey, did any of the parents
      get video yesterday?

36:11.703 --> 36:12.836
       Yep, all of them.

36:13.205 --> 36:15.205
  Oh, I'll call Rachel's mom.

36:15.674 --> 36:17.741
No, it's okay. I sucked anyway.

36:17.943 --> 36:19.476
   I'm sure that's not true.

36:23.515 --> 36:24.447
        [doorbell rings]

36:24.449 --> 36:29.352
  No, let your mother get it.
    She needs the practice.

36:31.623 --> 36:32.556
          I'll do it!

36:39.498 --> 36:40.630
              -Hi.
              -Hi.

36:43.669 --> 36:44.834
           [both] Hi.

36:44.903 --> 36:47.237
           [laughing]

36:47.873 --> 36:53.810
        -What are you--
      -Oh, I just stopped
        by to say hello.

36:56.682 --> 36:57.647
      Before the viewing.

36:57.649 --> 36:59.783
    Oh, no. Another funeral.

37:01.453 --> 37:03.787
             -Yeah.
 -Did you know Ann-Marie well?

37:03.789 --> 37:06.790
Oh, she was a distant relative.

37:08.327 --> 37:09.426
      Really very distant.

37:12.564 --> 37:14.431
 Well, the viewing is that way.

37:14.433 --> 37:17.634
Oh yeah, I remember. [chuckles]

37:17.636 --> 37:21.938
            -Sorry.
    -And if there's anything
          I can do...

37:24.509 --> 37:26.343
        Okay, thank you.

37:42.728 --> 37:43.660
              Oh.

37:44.730 --> 37:45.662
              Hey.

37:47.332 --> 37:48.265
              Hi.

37:54.539 --> 37:55.538
         How'd she die?

37:57.609 --> 37:58.775
      I'm not really sure.

38:00.912 --> 38:04.347
   So, she's not family then?

38:05.784 --> 38:07.284
            No, no.

38:10.022 --> 38:10.954
           A friend?

38:12.591 --> 38:14.524
       Yeah, not exactly.

38:17.496 --> 38:18.495
          Who is she?

38:19.364 --> 38:23.500
      Oh, Ann-Marie Toddy.

38:25.070 --> 38:26.436
        You don't really
       know her, do you?

38:26.638 --> 38:31.041
      I wanted to see your
         mother again,

38:31.043 --> 38:32.642
    and when she opened the
       door, I panicked.

38:33.879 --> 38:36.313
      You've been here for
      a really long time.

38:38.016 --> 38:39.015
          Five hours.

38:40.419 --> 38:41.451
           Oh my God.

38:41.953 --> 38:42.952
   Well, I was going to leave

38:42.954 --> 38:44.054
    when her family came in,

38:44.690 --> 38:45.789
      and nobody ever did.

38:46.892 --> 38:47.824
            Nobody.

38:54.066 --> 38:55.332
  [Peter] Bunions bugging ya?

38:57.002 --> 38:58.535
     I don't have bunions.

38:59.438 --> 39:00.403
       Just my feet hurt.

39:00.405 --> 39:03.707
    Yeah, that's because you
     always buy your shoes
     a half size too small.

39:03.709 --> 39:04.808
    I'm a seven and a half.

39:04.810 --> 39:06.509
      No, you're an eight.

39:06.511 --> 39:07.744
    Let me see them bunions.

39:08.480 --> 39:11.514
[gasps] You don't have bunions.

39:11.516 --> 39:13.383
   You just got perfect feet.

39:13.685 --> 39:14.818
          [chuckling]

39:14.820 --> 39:15.752
      Let me massage them.

39:16.054 --> 39:17.053
   I have to go back to work.

39:17.055 --> 39:18.688
      Oh, come on, Molls.

39:18.690 --> 39:20.090
         Five minutes.

39:20.092 --> 39:21.591
  I know you miss my massages,

39:21.593 --> 39:22.659
   don't act like you don't.

39:23.428 --> 39:24.627
    What were you watching?

39:28.900 --> 39:31.000
       -[Molly] <i> No shoes!</i>
        -[Peter] <i> Right?</i>

39:32.738 --> 39:34.104
 <i> Come on, Mommy, dance with us!</i>

39:34.106 --> 39:35.105
 [Molly] <i> You want me to dance?</i>

39:35.107 --> 39:36.539
 <i> Who's going to take the video?</i>

39:36.541 --> 39:39.109
 <i> Who cares? Just dance with us!</i>

39:39.644 --> 39:41.978
        -[Peter] <i> Dance!</i>
      -[Molly] <i> All right,</i>
      <i> we're going to spin.</i>

39:43.048 --> 39:44.781
         <i> Get in there.</i>

39:44.783 --> 39:46.149
 [Molly] <i> Come here, baby girl.</i>
         <i> Dance with me.</i>

39:47.886 --> 39:49.853
 Wow, where did you find that?

39:51.490 --> 39:52.589
             To us.

39:52.590 --> 39:53.689
       -[Peter laughing]
  -It's not even five o'clock.

39:53.692 --> 39:55.658
 It's after midnight in Moscow.

39:57.596 --> 39:58.528
              Mm.

40:00.532 --> 40:01.464
        Come on, Molls.

40:06.838 --> 40:08.738
             -Yeah.
          -[laughing]

40:08.740 --> 40:10.473
          Yes. Right?

40:12.711 --> 40:14.411
 Why do you think nobody came?

40:14.813 --> 40:16.479
      You're not actually
        her family, Joe.

40:16.481 --> 40:18.515
      I don't think you're
      allowed to do that.

40:19.184 --> 40:20.917
       Well, if they ever
        show up for her,

40:21.620 --> 40:22.886
   they can tell me to stop.

40:24.923 --> 40:28.525
       Remember my thesis
       project in Moscow?

40:29.461 --> 40:31.761
  That tiny sixth floor flat.

40:32.564 --> 40:36.766
  I mean, we just had to heat
   our water up on the stove
    just to take a hot bath.

40:37.636 --> 40:39.536
   Except for that one crazy
        day in November.

40:40.472 --> 40:43.873
   All of a sudden, this flat
   with no hot water heater,

40:44.609 --> 40:45.642
       the water ran hot.

40:47.879 --> 40:49.012
     I took a bath all day.

40:49.014 --> 40:52.549
     Just kept filling the
     tub up with hot water
       until it ran out.

40:54.686 --> 40:55.852
 That's the night we made Sam.

40:56.488 --> 40:57.854
  Do you want to go on a date?

40:59.691 --> 41:00.623
           With you?

41:03.462 --> 41:05.562
         No. [chuckles]

41:05.564 --> 41:07.063
     That would be illegal.

41:09.534 --> 41:10.667
          With my mom.

41:11.970 --> 41:13.636
That is why you're here, right?
         You like her?

41:16.741 --> 41:18.842
          [chuckling]

41:18.844 --> 41:19.776
             I do.

41:21.213 --> 41:22.779
        So then ask her.

41:24.149 --> 41:27.183
    It's been a pretty long
       time for me, Sam.

41:27.986 --> 41:29.519
Well, you can't keep pretending

41:29.521 --> 41:31.955
      like you're a friend
         or a relative

41:31.957 --> 41:34.224
   of every recently deceased
        person in town.

41:35.060 --> 41:35.992
            Why not?

41:37.796 --> 41:39.662
         Just ask her.

41:40.131 --> 41:41.064
             Look.

41:43.101 --> 41:45.568
      Ann-Marie Toddy even
   thinks you should ask her.
             Look.

41:46.705 --> 41:49.572
       [in a deep voice]
       Go on a date, Joe.

41:49.841 --> 41:51.541
             -Sam!
             -Joe.

41:55.046 --> 41:57.046
             -Okay.
       -Wait, seriously?

41:58.283 --> 41:59.282
      Then let's go right
         now, come on.

41:59.284 --> 42:00.917
           No, stop.

42:02.954 --> 42:06.589
       That's something I
    should do alone, thanks.

42:06.591 --> 42:08.191
     Okay, I'll go get her
  before you change your mind.

42:08.193 --> 42:09.125
            No, Sam!

42:10.795 --> 42:11.728
              Mom?

42:14.199 --> 42:15.131
              Mom?

42:16.167 --> 42:17.100
              Mom?

42:17.102 --> 42:19.669
      -What are you doing?
      -What are you doing?

42:19.671 --> 42:20.603
            Get out!

42:22.607 --> 42:23.540
              Oh.

42:28.713 --> 42:30.713
           [laughing]

42:43.094 --> 42:44.027
         [Peter] Molly.

42:49.834 --> 42:50.867
    You should get dressed.

42:58.777 --> 43:00.043
      You kept my clothes?

43:00.045 --> 43:00.977
             Yeah.

43:02.080 --> 43:03.246
        Ah, I love you.

43:10.188 --> 43:11.254
          Molly, hey.

43:11.256 --> 43:13.089
              -Hi.
           -Hi, Mom.

43:13.091 --> 43:14.123
           Samantha.

43:14.826 --> 43:16.092
        Now? Uh, Molly.

43:17.596 --> 43:18.328
        I was wondering,

43:19.331 --> 43:21.864
           [mumbling]

43:22.701 --> 43:24.667
 I was just wondering if uh...

43:25.670 --> 43:26.903
   Who paid for the funeral?

43:31.710 --> 43:34.110
      She did. In advance.

43:35.046 --> 43:36.879
    It was very nice of you
     to stay the whole day.

43:37.215 --> 43:39.816
Oh, it wasn't quite the whole...

43:42.087 --> 43:43.252
      Would you like to go
     out with me sometime?

43:47.726 --> 43:49.626
            -Go out?
          -On a date.

43:49.628 --> 43:51.027
    I got it from here, Sam.

43:54.265 --> 43:55.198
             Oh...

43:56.001 --> 43:57.000
          Hello, Joe.

43:57.802 --> 44:01.304
Joe, I would like that, really,

44:04.075 --> 44:05.742
       but going out is a
   little bit tricky for me.

44:05.977 --> 44:06.909
              Why?

44:07.679 --> 44:08.978
        Yeah, Mom. Why?

44:09.114 --> 44:10.046
           There's...

44:10.048 --> 44:12.315
   For one thing, my mother's
         not very well.

44:12.317 --> 44:14.017
        I am just fine.

44:14.019 --> 44:16.319
     -Yeah, you should go.
           -Go where?

44:16.321 --> 44:17.787
      On a date with Joe.

44:17.789 --> 44:19.288
           God, yes.

44:19.290 --> 44:20.723
         Have some fun.

44:20.725 --> 44:22.058
            -Friday?
             -6:30?

44:22.694 --> 44:23.426
          It's a date.

44:24.262 --> 44:26.963
      [lighthearted music]

44:27.932 --> 44:29.832
  Oh shit, I'll be right back.

44:33.772 --> 44:36.139
    I may not have done this
in a while, but I'm pretty sure
         that was a no.

44:37.308 --> 44:39.976
Mom! You just walked out on him.

44:39.978 --> 44:41.177
   I can't do this right now.

44:41.179 --> 44:42.311
    You should have knocked!

44:42.981 --> 44:44.447
Seriously? That's your response?

44:44.449 --> 44:46.849
   I do not want to have this
     conversation with you.

44:46.851 --> 44:49.786
 I can go my whole life without
   having this conversation.

44:49.788 --> 44:50.853
       I am your mother,

44:50.855 --> 44:54.323
 and I have feelings and needs.

44:54.325 --> 44:56.693
       He was meant to be
        a gag gift, Mom.

44:56.695 --> 44:58.127
        Not a boyfriend.

44:58.129 --> 44:59.462
   Please just do it for me!

44:59.464 --> 45:00.830
            -Molly--
             -Okay.

45:02.767 --> 45:03.700
             Okay?

45:03.702 --> 45:04.467
            Really?

45:06.137 --> 45:08.905
   Um, then I'll pick you up.

45:08.907 --> 45:10.907
 Does Friday, 6:30 still work?

45:12.410 --> 45:15.311
   Seven. I volunteer at the
        animal shelter,

45:15.313 --> 45:17.113
   my first shift is Friday.

45:18.083 --> 45:19.082
         See you then?

45:20.218 --> 45:21.150
         See you then.

45:25.190 --> 45:26.122
          [chuckling]

45:26.725 --> 45:28.191
      What just happened?

45:28.326 --> 45:31.928
   You have a real, live date
   with a real, live person.

45:34.132 --> 45:35.064
    We need to get to work.

45:35.467 --> 45:36.399
            On what?

45:37.001 --> 45:37.934
           The plan.

45:42.407 --> 45:43.372
    Oh honey, fix your hair.

45:44.509 --> 45:45.842
             -Why?
 -[grandma] It's in your eyes.

45:45.844 --> 45:48.311
     Welcome to your online
         support group.

45:48.780 --> 45:50.346
    Everyone, this is Molly.

45:50.348 --> 45:52.181
     Mom, this is everyone.

45:52.183 --> 45:53.883
      [people] <i> Hi, Molly.</i>

45:54.185 --> 45:55.351
Oh, you've got to be kidding me.

45:56.454 --> 45:59.255
   [support group] <i> Hi, Molly.</i>

46:00.825 --> 46:01.758
           Hi, Molls.

46:01.826 --> 46:04.160
        [laughing] What?

46:04.162 --> 46:06.929
    <i> I got tired of not being</i>
    <i> able to go to the movies</i>

46:06.931 --> 46:09.098
    <i> or driving 15 miles away</i>

46:09.100 --> 46:11.100
    <i> just to avoid a freeway.</i>

46:11.102 --> 46:13.269
  <i> Life got so small, you know?</i>

46:13.271 --> 46:14.437
       No, we don't know.

46:14.439 --> 46:18.141
       <i> Guys, today I went</i>
      <i> and got a pedicure.</i>

46:18.977 --> 46:21.944
     <i> Next week, I'm getting</i>
      <i> the other foot done.</i>

46:22.046 --> 46:22.979
           [laughing]

46:23.181 --> 46:25.348
Baby steps. One foot at a time.

46:26.117 --> 46:29.786
-[woman] <i> Molly? What about you?</i>
        -What about me?

46:29.921 --> 46:32.388
  <i> Is there anything you would</i>
 <i> like to share with the group?</i>

46:32.390 --> 46:34.123
             Molls.

46:34.125 --> 46:35.458
      You're nothing like
         these losers.

46:36.895 --> 46:38.861
     No, I don't think so.

46:39.030 --> 46:39.962
              Yes!

46:40.365 --> 46:43.966
 [speaking in foreign language]

46:45.236 --> 46:47.053
          [chuckling]

46:47.054 --> 46:48.871
  <i> ¶ Pick me up, shake me up ¶</i>

46:48.873 --> 46:52.074
         <i> ¶ Turn it up,</i>
      <i> Just make it loud ¶</i>

46:52.076 --> 46:54.310
  <i> ¶ Can't stop, stop me now ¶</i>

46:54.312 --> 46:56.212
           <i> ¶ Oh no ¶</i>

46:56.214 --> 46:57.146
       You're doing good!

46:58.016 --> 46:58.948
        A little faster.

47:00.318 --> 47:01.450
     A little faster, yes.

47:03.855 --> 47:04.854
           [knocking]

47:05.323 --> 47:07.490
  <i> ¶ Can't stop, stop me now ¶</i>

47:07.492 --> 47:10.026
         <i> ¶ Oh no, oh ¶</i>

47:10.995 --> 47:11.928
            Come in.

47:14.532 --> 47:16.232
              Hey!
 Do you want to play Scrabble?

47:16.234 --> 47:22.004
     Oh, I don't think so.
  I'm going to stay and finish
   the book that you gave me.

47:22.006 --> 47:25.441
        -Oh, how is it?
  -Good, I knew it would help.

47:25.443 --> 47:27.476
   Oh, I have to run out for
    a second. Lotto tickets.

47:28.246 --> 47:29.445
 You're not going to win, Mom.

47:30.415 --> 47:32.415
        Hey! It's okay,
       we can play later.

47:32.417 --> 47:34.083
  She's not going to win, Sam.

47:34.085 --> 47:36.319
    Well, somebody's got to.

47:36.321 --> 47:38.187
      Thank you, Sam. Hm!

47:43.328 --> 47:45.228
  Man, I'm glad they're gone.

47:45.897 --> 47:47.930
      I promised them I'd
       finish this book.

47:49.300 --> 47:51.534
     There's so many other
       productive things

47:51.536 --> 47:53.102
  we could be doing right now.

47:54.105 --> 47:55.037
           Like what?

47:56.941 --> 47:58.341
      I think you need to
       cancel that date.

47:59.010 --> 48:00.209
     I think you're right.

48:00.211 --> 48:01.143
             Yeah.

48:04.349 --> 48:07.884
  <i> ¶ Pick me up, shake me up ¶</i>

48:07.886 --> 48:11.020
         <i> ¶ Turn it up,</i>
      <i> Just make it loud ¶</i>

48:11.022 --> 48:13.289
  <i> ¶ Can't stop, stop me now ¶</i>

48:13.291 --> 48:17.493
         <i> ¶ Oh no, oh ¶</i>

48:17.495 --> 48:20.630
  <i> ¶ Pick me up, shake me up ¶</i>

48:20.632 --> 48:24.166
   <i> ¶ No, it ain't over now ¶</i>

48:24.168 --> 48:26.402
  <i> ¶ Can't stop, stop me now ¶</i>

48:26.404 --> 48:29.405
         <i> ¶ Oh no, oh ¶</i>

48:29.407 --> 48:30.339
       Come back inside.

48:32.377 --> 48:33.910
             -But--
          -I miss you.

48:46.624 --> 48:47.590
          You did it!

48:51.562 --> 48:53.596
   [Sam] With the first pair,
    you got like 100 points.

48:53.598 --> 48:55.598
         [grandma] So,
  can you feel the cool breeze

48:55.600 --> 48:56.666
       washing over you?

48:56.668 --> 49:00.469
  -[Molly] A little bit, yes?
      -[grandma] And then
     the sunlight's on you.

49:02.206 --> 49:03.706
Everything's peaceful and calm.

49:04.375 --> 49:06.575
     You're coasting along
       on the bike ride.

49:06.577 --> 49:08.210
      Soon you'll be doing
         this with Sam.

49:08.212 --> 49:09.712
    Won't that be wonderful?

49:09.714 --> 49:12.248
       Every time you do
       a step like this,

49:12.250 --> 49:13.983
      you're a step closer
      to freeing yourself.

49:14.719 --> 49:17.453
         [catchy music]

49:35.540 --> 49:38.007
      I have a plan to go
        out this weekend

49:38.476 --> 49:40.209
      on a date, actually.

49:40.211 --> 49:42.178
       <i> That's incredible!</i>

49:42.180 --> 49:43.346
    <i> Molly, that's wonderful.</i>

49:43.348 --> 49:45.581
  I've thought about canceling
      it about 100 times,

49:45.583 --> 49:47.183
     but I haven't yet, so.

49:47.185 --> 49:48.584
       <i> You didn't cancel.</i>

49:48.586 --> 49:50.353
      <i> That's huge, Molly.</i>

49:50.688 --> 49:53.422
 [woman] <i> You should be really,</i>
   <i> really proud of yourself.</i>

49:54.058 --> 49:56.659
     <i> Do you have a plan in</i>
      <i> mind for the night?</i>

49:57.095 --> 49:58.327
 I have a plan, I have a plan.

50:00.098 --> 50:02.665
         -I got to go.
     <i> -Wait, you're so close</i>
        <i> to a breakthr--</i>

50:02.667 --> 50:04.567
         Yes! Let's go!

50:05.169 --> 50:07.069
 [grandma] Honey, you got this!
     I know you can do it.

50:07.171 --> 50:09.005
     Yes, you got it, Mom.

50:09.007 --> 50:10.406
        -[Sam] Come on!
  -[grandma] You got it, Mom.

50:10.408 --> 50:11.640
           [cheering]

50:11.642 --> 50:12.575
           Oh my God!

50:12.577 --> 50:15.344
  <i> ¶ Pick me up, shake me up ¶</i>

50:15.346 --> 50:17.613
           [cheering]

50:19.250 --> 50:21.350
  <i> ¶ Can't stop, stop me now ¶</i>

50:21.352 --> 50:24.286
       [excited yelling]

50:25.423 --> 50:26.689
       Did you see that?

50:26.691 --> 50:28.424
   Yeah, what's the big deal?

50:29.060 --> 50:30.426
        I went outside!

50:30.528 --> 50:32.294
         I was outside!

50:32.296 --> 50:34.463
     For like ten seconds.

50:35.066 --> 50:37.733
     Wow, congratulations.

50:39.337 --> 50:40.436
      Don't be like that.

50:49.380 --> 50:50.679
   Where are your cuff links?

50:54.152 --> 50:55.084
          Hey, Frank.

50:55.086 --> 50:57.386
       I'm missing a pair
         of cuff links.

50:58.156 --> 51:00.222
       -I'll look around.
       -Okay, thank you.

51:02.660 --> 51:04.093
   Didn't have a girlfriend?

51:05.229 --> 51:06.162
           Boyfriend?

51:09.067 --> 51:11.434
     How many dates did you
       go on in 25 years?

51:13.271 --> 51:14.537
  I'm going on a date tonight.

51:16.541 --> 51:17.506
         I know, right?

51:19.410 --> 51:20.342
         I'm terrified.

51:22.313 --> 51:23.779
 I don't remember how to do it.

51:26.651 --> 51:27.616
       How do you do it?

51:32.457 --> 51:33.756
       Well, what's wrong
         with that one?

51:33.758 --> 51:35.591
  [Molly] God, it's so purple.

